  "prompt": "Which is the best brand suit to wear in India?",
  "response": "Choosing the best brand for a suit in India depends on various factors such as budget, occasion, personal style, and fit preferences. Here are some of the top brands known for their quality suits in India:\n\n---\n\n### **Luxury Brands** (High-End, Premium Suits)\n1. **Canali**  \n   - Known for impeccable tailoring and luxurious fabrics.\n   - Ideal for formal events and business meetings.\n\n2. **Armani**  \n   - Offers sleek, modern designs with a focus on elegance and sophistication.\n   - Perfect for high-profile events.\n\n3. **Hugo Boss**  \n   - Combines contemporary styles with classic tailoring.\n   - Great for both formal and semi-formal occasions.\n\n4. **Zegna**  \n   - Renowned for premium fabrics and timeless designs.\n   - A top choice for discerning professionals.\n\n---\n\n### **Mid-Range Brands** (Affordable Luxury)\n1. **Blackberrys**  \n   - Offers well-tailored suits with a modern fit.\n   - Popular among professionals and wedding-goers.\n\n2. **Raymond**  \n   - A trusted Indian brand with a wide range of suits for all occasions.\n   - Known for quality fabrics and traditional tailoring.\n\n3. **Van Heusen**  \n   - Focuses on contemporary styles and affordability.\n   - Suitable for office wear and casual events.\n\n4. **Peter England**  \n   - Budget-friendly suits with decent quality.\n   - Great for entry-level professionals.\n\n---\n\n### **Custom Suits** (Tailor-Made)\n1. **Manyavar**  \n   - Specializes in ethnic and fusion suits, particularly for weddings.\n   - Offers a blend of traditional and modern designs.\n\n2. **Sartaj**  \n   - Known for custom-made suits with attention to detail.\n   - Ideal for weddings and special occasions.\n\n3. **Tailorman**  \n   - A premium custom tailoring brand offering personalized suits.\n   - Perfect for those who want a perfect fit and unique design.\n\n---\n\n### **Factors to Consider When Choosing a Suit Brand**  \n- **Occasion**: Choose formal brands like Canali or Zegna for business, and brands like Manyavar for weddings.  \n- **Fit**: Opt for brands that offer slim-fit, tailored, or custom options based on your body type.  \n- **Budget**: Decide whether you want luxury, mid-range, or budget-friendly suits.  \n- **Fabric**: Look for wool, linen, or blended fabrics depending on the season and comfort.  \n\n---\n\nUltimately, the \"best\" brand depends on your specific needs and preferences. If you're unsure, visiting a store or consulting with a tailor can help you make the right choice.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
